Power minister Veerappa Moily told reporters that by this morning power had been fully restored across the country.

Mr
Moily, who took over the top power position yesterday, said an 
investigation into the crisis had been launched and he did not want to 
point fingers or speculate about the cause.

Other officials said the blackout might have been the result of states drawing too much power from the grid.

Some
analysts dismissed that explanation, saying that if overdrawing power 
from the grid caused this kind of collapse, it would happen all the 
time.

